==English==

===Etymology===
From the name of '''Soshangani''', the leader of the Revolt against [[Chaka]] [[Zulu]], who fled to [[Zimbabwe]]. Alternatively from Zulu: ''shangane'': a wanderer.

===Proper Noun===
{{en-noun|[[Shangani]]|or [[Shangans]]}}
# An African [[tribe]] or [[clan]] or [[nation]].
# A member of the tribe.
# The language of the Shangaan.
#* There are up to 14 minority dialects in the country, which include [[Kalanga]] spoken in Bulilimamangwe district in Matabeleland South, [[Hwesa]] in the Nyanga district, [[Sotho]] in Gwanda South, '''Shangani''' in Chiredzi, [[Chitoko-Tonga]] (Mudzi Tonga) in Mudzi district, [[Venda]] in Beitbridge and [[Tonga]] in the Binga, Omay and Nyaminyami districts. [http://listserv.arizona.edu/cgi-bin/wa?A2=ind0405&L=ilat&D=0&P=1731 - 18k -]

====Usage note====
'''Shangaans''' is a sub standard spelling of the plural. '''Shangani''' is the preferred plural. '''Shangans''' is an alternative accepted plural.

